The paper focuses on software restructuring, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of metrics to evaluate cohesion and coupling also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The analysis of a real case also implies a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and complex systems (cs.CY).
